{
  "texts": [
    "Models like ChatGPT lack the ability to access information from an external memory or database, leading to potential inaccuracies in recall of facts.",
    "However, because these programs generate images and text based on statistical patterns, rather than gaining a true understanding of the world, they are prone to fabricating facts and repeating hateful and biased statements (e.g.",
    "12 and 13 show some example factual failures of ChatGPT.",
    "For instance, ChatGPT claims that Abacus is faster than DNA computing for deep learning (See here).ChatGPT struggles to differentiate between factual information and fiction and creates imaginary information (Fig. 14).",
    "While this is a challenge that humans face as well, they at least comprehend the distinction between the two.It is important to exercise caution when using language models like LLMs as they have only acquired a limited and superficial understanding of human knowledge and may not provide accurate factual information."
  ]
}